06/03/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Deputy Prime Minister for European Integration Gordana Djurovic announced on Monday (March 5th) that the government has prepared an action plan to meet the recommendations of the new European Partnership with Montenegro directive.
Djurovic met on Monday with the members of a European Commission screening team, who have begun a five-day visit to Podgorica.
They discussed the short and medium-term priority tasks outlined in the directive that was adopted in January.
Djurovic also announced that a state commission would be established shortly, to co-ordinate implementation of a government strategy against organised crime and corruption.
(Vijesti, Mina - 06/03/07)
